WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.857 --> 00:00:03.940
FEMALE SPEAKER: Thank you
everyone for being here.

00:00:03.940 --> 00:00:04.730
Welcome today.

00:00:06.010 --> 00:00:09.925
In 1986, Massimo Bottura
bought a roadside trattoria.

00:00:09.925 --> 00:00:13.000
He had no culinary
training and no experience.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:14.900
Despite this, the
restaurant, which

00:00:14.900 --> 00:00:17.695
served traditional Emilian
dishes, was a great success.

00:00:18.910 --> 00:00:22.340
In 1993, Alain Ducasse
visited the trattoria

00:00:22.340 --> 00:00:26.740
and invited Massimo to cook at
Hotel de Paris in Monte Carlo.

00:00:26.740 --> 00:00:28.970
After this life-changing
experience--

00:00:28.970 --> 00:00:31.750
imagine going from a trattoria
to a three Michelin star

00:00:31.750 --> 00:00:34.680
restaurant-- he opened
a new restaurant,

00:00:34.680 --> 00:00:39.460
Osteria Francescana, in
Modena's Historic Center.

00:00:39.460 --> 00:00:41.340
He was no longer cooking
traditional recipes,

00:00:41.340 --> 00:00:43.090
but provocative
Italian renditions,

00:00:43.090 --> 00:00:45.030
which were received with
skepticism and doubt.

00:00:46.410 --> 00:00:49.120
In fact, it took 10 years from
receiving his first Michelin

00:00:49.120 --> 00:00:53.020
star in 2001 to receiving his
third star, Michelin's highest

00:00:53.020 --> 00:00:54.980
rating, in 2012.

00:00:54.980 --> 00:00:56.090
Why?

00:00:56.090 --> 00:00:58.740
Because in Italy, the idea
of tradition and evolution

00:00:58.740 --> 00:01:00.195
is not easy for
anyone to accept.

00:01:01.330 --> 00:01:03.960
Today, the restaurant is
rated the best in Italy.

00:01:03.960 --> 00:01:06.400
And for the second
consecutive year,

00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:10.070
Osteria Francescana ranked
third in San Pellegrino's list

00:01:10.070 --> 00:01:13.000
of the world's 50
best restaurants.

00:01:14.530 --> 00:01:17.190
Massimo's food blends
tradition with innovation,

00:01:17.190 --> 00:01:20.120
managing to capture the essence
of classic Italian dishes

00:01:20.120 --> 00:01:21.980
via modern expressions.

00:01:21.980 --> 00:01:23.500
One of the ways he
achieves this is

00:01:23.500 --> 00:01:25.870
by marrying his passion
for food with his love

00:01:25.870 --> 00:01:27.790
of contemporary art.

00:01:27.790 --> 00:01:29.410
He is also known for
the playful names

00:01:29.410 --> 00:01:31.770
he gives his dishes,
like a signature dish,

00:01:31.770 --> 00:01:33.150
Oops, I Dropped the Lemon Tart.

00:01:34.200 --> 00:01:36.240
Earlier this week,
on Jimmy Kimmel,

00:01:36.240 --> 00:01:39.820
he made and fed Jimmy his iconic
recipe, Memory of a Mortadella

00:01:39.820 --> 00:01:40.320
Sandwich.

00:01:42.040 --> 00:01:43.880
We have a three-minute
video to show you now

00:01:43.880 --> 00:01:46.840
of Massimo in his
restaurant in Modena, Italy.

00:01:48.322 --> 00:01:49.350
