00:01:54.820 --> 00:02:01.094
-I'm born and I grew up in the
land of fast car and slow food.

00:02:03.950 --> 00:02:07.690
I learned, since I was a
kid, to think very quick.

00:02:07.690 --> 00:02:10.560
As the Roman they were
saying, think quick.

00:02:10.560 --> 00:02:12.455
Do it very quick, but slowly.

00:02:15.920 --> 00:02:20.680
That means have a very quick
thought, but do it slowly.

00:02:20.680 --> 00:02:24.850
Because you need a lot
of time to do something.

00:02:24.850 --> 00:02:28.107
They interpret
what I'm thinking,

00:02:28.107 --> 00:02:29.440
and they know what I'm thinking.

00:02:31.938 --> 00:02:32.872
So here we go.

00:02:34.740 --> 00:02:37.132
Oops, We Dropped the Lemon Tart.

00:02:41.770 --> 00:02:47.121
Food, for Italians, is like
the soccer team, or the Pope,

00:02:47.121 --> 00:02:48.880
or the food-- in order.

00:02:48.880 --> 00:02:51.260
Soccer team first, Pope
second, tradition third.

00:02:52.940 --> 00:02:55.880
I remember all these
gastronomic trips

00:02:55.880 --> 00:02:58.670
I took with my older
brothers because my mom was

00:02:58.670 --> 00:03:00.740
pushing me-- go, go, go.

00:03:00.740 --> 00:03:02.460
Don't just play soccer.

00:03:02.460 --> 00:03:04.215
Because I was playing
soccer every day.

00:03:05.370 --> 00:03:08.395
I think of those
kinds of experiences--

00:03:08.395 --> 00:03:11.380
they were a totally
important part of my life.

00:03:11.380 --> 00:03:14.060
Because going on Mont
Saint-Michel or [? Angelo ?]

00:03:14.060 --> 00:03:16.840
[? Gallo ?] visiting
the wine cellar.

00:03:16.840 --> 00:03:21.090
Drive to Nice, eat
oyster, get drunk,

00:03:21.090 --> 00:03:22.290
going back for the night.

00:03:23.880 --> 00:03:27.160
And say Mom, but Massimo,
where have you been?

00:03:27.160 --> 00:03:28.530
Uh, studying.

00:03:28.530 --> 00:03:29.840
[ITALIAN]

00:03:32.180 --> 00:03:34.460
How can I forget about
the taste of lasagna?

00:03:35.980 --> 00:03:37.270
It's impossible.

00:03:37.270 --> 00:03:40.450
Or the piece of
Parmesan, or a drop

00:03:40.450 --> 00:03:42.810
of 50 years old
balsamic vinegar.

00:03:42.810 --> 00:03:44.500
That's magic.

00:03:44.500 --> 00:03:48.530
So what we have to do is
just that see everything

00:03:48.530 --> 00:03:51.820
from the distance, see what's
wrong and what's right,

00:03:51.820 --> 00:03:54.980
and bring just the best
part into the future.

00:03:57.560 --> 00:04:01.330
The book is going to be about
my passion, the evolution

00:04:01.330 --> 00:04:07.410
of my ideas-- food, a
dose of art, and music.

00:04:07.410 --> 00:04:10.650
Maybe, as I always
said, through passion,

00:04:10.650 --> 00:04:12.820
I'm going to transfer emotions.

00:04:12.820 --> 00:04:16.829
Maybe the book, at the end,
is going to be about emotion.

00:04:16.829 --> 00:04:17.630
I don't know.

00:04:17.630 --> 00:04:18.269
I hope so.

00:04:21.070 --> 00:04:24.310
Get deep into things is one
of the most important things.

00:04:24.310 --> 00:04:27.060
I hope people that
are going to read--

00:04:27.060 --> 00:04:29.850
how is the structure
of creativity,

00:04:29.850 --> 00:04:32.280
and they're going to be
inspired by this structure.

00:04:33.980 --> 00:04:34.850
Express yourself.

00:04:34.850 --> 00:04:35.991
That's the point.

00:04:35.991 --> 00:04:36.490
Feel free.

00:04:36.490 --> 00:04:36.990
Be brave.

00:04:37.750 --> 00:04:40.680
I always say to
the young chef, be

00:04:40.680 --> 00:04:43.280
